8.
About the job
Key Responsibilities

1) Corporate & Business Strategy

Develop long-term strategic roadmaps for renewable power generation, storage, and integrated energy solutions.
Support leadership in defining growth priorities, market entry strategies, and expansion plans.
Conduct scenario planning and strategic forecasting for the evolving energy landscape.
2) Market & Competitive Intelligence

Track global and domestic renewable energy trends, policies, and technologies.
Perform competitor benchmarking and market sizing across solar, wind, storage, green hydrogen, and emerging energy technologies.
Identify new business opportunities, partnerships, and investment areas.
3) Investment & Business Case Development

Build financial models and techno-commercial business cases for new projects and acquisitions.
Support M&A evaluations, partnerships, and joint ventures.
Prepare board-level presentations and investment memos.
4) Strategic Projects & Transformation

Lead cross-functional strategic initiatives across engineering, finance, project development, and commercial teams.
Drive strategic reviews and performance tracking of key RE programs.
Translate strategy into actionable implementation roadmaps.
5) Stakeholder & Leadership Support

Work closely with senior leadership on strategic decision-making.
Prepare executive dashboards, insights, and recommendations.
Coordinate with internal and external stakeholders, consultants, and partners.
Candidate Profile

Education

MBA/PGDM from Tier-1 / Premium B-Schools (IIMs, ISB, XLRI, FMS, SPJIMR, etc.)
Engineering background preferred but not mandatory.
Experience

2–6 years of experience in strategy consulting, corporate strategy, energy consulting, investment banking, or renewable energy.
Experience in energy, infrastructure, utilities, or sustainability sectors is highly desirable.
Skills & Competencies

Strong strategic thinking and problem-solving skills.
Advanced financial modelling and business case development.
Excellent research, analytical, and presentation skills.
Ability to manage complex cross-functional projects.
Strong communication and stakeholder management capabilities.

