9.
About the job
About the role

We’re looking for a Strategy Consultant to lead 0→1 strategic initiatives across Stable Money — identifying opportunities, building solutions from the ground up, and driving them through launch and early stabilization.

This role is designed for builders who enjoy tackling ambiguous problems, creating structure where none exists, and then transitioning initiatives into steady-state ownership before moving on to the next challenge. You’ll work closely with leadership and cross-functional teams to shape and execute high-impact business priorities.

Responsibilities

0→1 Initiative Leadership

Identify, evaluate, and shape new business opportunities, products, or operational models
Translate ambiguous problem spaces into structured execution plans
Drive initiatives from concept and validation through launch and early scaling
Establish operating rhythms, KPIs, and ownership structures for continuity
Initiative Ownership

Drive end-to-end execution of strategic initiatives — from concept through launch and stabilization
Define success metrics, execution plans, and operating cadences
Remove execution bottlenecks and ensure momentum toward milestones
Cross-Functional Execution

Partner with product, growth, operations, finance, and external stakeholders
Drive alignment across teams to meet milestones
Remove blockers and maintain execution velocity
What we’re looking for

Graduate/Post Graduate from tier 1 colleges (IITs/IIMs)
2–5 years experience in strategy, consulting, business ops, or related roles at top consulting companies (MBB)
Demonstrated experience owning 0→1 projects or launches
Strong structured thinking and analytical rigor
Comfort operating in ambiguous, fast-moving environments
High ownership mindset and bias toward action
Nice to have

Experience in fintech, consumer tech, or marketplaces
Startup or consulting background
Exposure to product or business incubation environments
Why join us

Opportunity to build and shape initiatives from scratch
Work across a portfolio of strategic priorities
Direct exposure to leadership and decision-making
Dynamic environment with continuous problem-solving

